  "abstract": "Soil carbonates, primarily calcium carbonate and dolomite, are key regulators of soil pH and carbon cycling, commonly quantified by acid dissolution and CO₂ measurement or equivalent calcium carbonate determination. Understanding soil carbonate content is essential for evaluating soil chemistry, fertility, and its role in the global carbon cycle.",
